  "elapsed_s": 185.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I do remember that when I left Germany, then we did a lot of investigation so that I took a train that crossed-- and, again, I don't remember the name of the-- of the town-- in a place where the quote 'old' unquote border police were still on duty, and not the new Nazi stormtrooper police.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Immediately, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was-- I do not recall seeing anything immediately, even though I might.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't recall it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What I do recall is-- is my general feeling of being in Germany in general, and being at home in particular.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It felt like being interned, like living in an institution that was surrounded by an invisible wall.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because you could be a complete human being only when you were inside your-- your own home or the homes of other Jews, or possibly the few real good friends.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The one really frightening experience I recall was that very soon after I arrived in Germany, and arrived with-- rather arrived at my parents' home, there was an order that all passports held by Jews had to be turned in to the authorities for some kooky purpose.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as much as I couldn't have possibly get a visa or leave the country without a passport, that with the most threatening thing that could have happened.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I lived through a couple of very scary weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was not until about two days or so after I had my appointment with the American consulate in Stuttgart that my passport was returned.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was returned.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, I assume that this was just a coincident, rather than just planned chicanery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it could very well have been, because they couldn't have made-- made me feel much worse than having-- being in Nazi Germany without a passport to leave.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
